<div id="review_2313837845" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2313837845" />
    <a title="Soplada" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/11469485-soplada"><img alt="Soplada" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1607178248p2/11469485.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2313837845?book_show_action=true">Mar 10, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Soplada" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Soplada" href="/user/show/11469485-soplada">Soplada</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2313837845" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1776006094833432777"><b><i>“A book must be the axe for the frozen sea within us. That is my belief.”</i>― Franz Kafka</b><br/><br/>If the book we read should tune in our deepest emotions, shake them out and extricate them hardly then this this story was the win.<br/><br/>There&apos;s a story behind everything, and yes, a cause, I thought about reading this book in the earlier years but this time was chosen for me to do so. The reality of the story.. the sense of reality in any story and the way you feel while you are being melt and mold with the words an</span>
  <span id="freeText1776006094833432777" style="display:none"><b><i>“A book must be the axe for the frozen sea within us. That is my belief.”</i>― Franz Kafka</b><br /><br />If the book we read should tune in our deepest emotions, shake them out and extricate them hardly then this this story was the win.<br /><br />There's a story behind everything, and yes, a cause, I thought about reading this book in the earlier years but this time was chosen for me to do so. The reality of the story.. the sense of reality in any story and the way you feel while you are being melt and mold with the words and pauses and the stops is what makes it a great story. and guess what? When it is the story of your mom and every mom..words cannot describe the unconditional love a mother can give. I hope it is not too late to realize how your parents melt to shape your life..<br />I hope it is never too late.. never ever to live your life and forgive yourself.<br /><br /><br />I like how the writer gives the sense of hope even after all things ended; in fiction everything is doable, and your passed away mother can visit you with her warm smile for one more day. But how beautiful is that you can spend more than just a day with your mothe touching her warm hands, smelling her pure perfume and be with her when the worlds is urging you and telling you to be away...<br />Why are we always waiting for the 'it is too late' moment?<br />This is the waft of the story... appreciate and realize with imagination... then live...<br /><br /><br />Thank you mister Mitch Albom, you always got me, you always hold that axe that broke the ice in the sea within me.<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="1776006094833432777" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


